      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When suffering feels this absolute and relentless, it's natural to question the purpose of enduring it. Your feelings about wanting the pain to cease are a direct response to unbearable physical distress, not a failing of character. Since your medical options seem exhausted, please speak with palliative care specialists; they focus specifically on managing intractable pain and improving quality of life when curative treatments stop working. They can offer comprehensive support tailored to severe, chronic suffering.",
